eraction. This paper completes the design and construction of a front-end and back-end separated e-commerce platform based on Spring Boot and Vue.js. The back-end adopts the Spring Boot framework, combined with MyBatis-Plus to achieve efficient data persistence, and optimizes database performance through the Druid connection pool. A stateless security authentication mechanism is established using Spring Security and JWT to ensure the security of user information and transactions. The system integrates Alipay SDK to realize the complete business cycle from product selection to online payment, and also incorporates forum community and activity reservation modules. By building a content ecosystem in the \"e-commerce + social\" model, it effectively enhances user stickiness and the interactive depth of the platform.\nIn strict accordance with software engineering development specifications, this paper discusses the whole process from requirement analysis, system design and function implementation to system testing. Test results show that the system stably supports core functions such as product display, shopping cart management, order processing and community interaction, and delivers favorable interactive experience and response speed. The development of this system provides small and medium-sized merchants with a low-cost and scalable solution for digital transformation, and also offers practical references for the integrated application of modern Web architectures in the e-commerce field','Given that the Internet and mobile payment technology are closely linked now, the previous single e-commerce system can no longer meet the new demands of high concurrency, easy operation, strong function integration, etc. The Design and Construction of a Front-end and Back-end Separated E-commerce Platform Based on Spring Boot and Vue.js are completed in this paper. Spring Boot is used on the back-end to get data from and write data to the Druid connection pool of the database via MyBatis-Plus. A stateless security authentication mechanism will be employed in Spring Security and JWT to protect the user\'s information and data. The entire business cycle of product selection and online payment in the system is built with the Alipay SDK, and it also has a forum community and activity reservation module. In order to enhance the power of sticking and using the platform, both e-commerce and social media will be combined.\nIn line with the software engineering development specifications, this paper will present all links in the process of requirement analysis, system design and function implementation, system testing, etc. According to the test results, the core functions of the system are working properly, such as displaying products, managing shopping carts, processing orders and operating communities, and there is a good sense of interactivity and response speed. The construction of this system can provide a low-cost and highly scalable way to achieve the digitalisation of small and medium-sized enterprises, and it can also offer some references for the integrated application of modern Web architecture in e-commerce.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,245,0.3675,'{\"cost\": 0.1078, \"success\": true, \"request_id\": \"678f7de5-8340-4762-8ed6-9327722f8694\", \"preset_name\": \"降AI260430_en\", \"preset_used\": \"aimove_weipu_english\", \"original_text\": \"With the deep integration of Internet technology and mobile payment, traditional monolithic e-commerce systems can hardly meet the current business demands for high concurrency, easy maintenance and strong interaction. This paper completes the design and construction of a front-end and back-end separated e-commerce platform based on Spring Boot and Vue.js. The back-end adopts the Spring Boot framework, combined with MyBatis-Plus to achieve efficient data persistence, and optimizes database performance through the Druid connection pool. A stateless security authentication mechanism is established using Spring Security and JWT to ensure the security of user information and transactions. The system integrates Alipay SDK to realize the complete business cycle from product selection to online payment, and also incorporates forum community and activity reservation modules. By building a content ecosystem in the \\\"e-commerce + social\\\" model, it effectively enhances user stickiness and the interactive depth of the platform.\\nIn strict accordance with software engineering development specifications, this paper discusses the whole process from requirement analysis, system design and function implementation to system testing. Test results show that the system stably supports core functions such as product display, shopping cart management, order processing and community interaction, and delivers favorable interactive experience and response speed. The development of this system provides small and medium-sized merchants with a low-cost and scalable solution for digital transformation, and also offers practical references for the integrated application of modern Web architectures in the e-commerce field\", \"processing_time\": 10.22, \"characters_count\": 245, \"paraphrased_text\": \"Given that the Internet and mobile payment technology are closely linked now, the previous single e-commerce system can no longer meet the new demands of high concurrency, easy operation, strong function integration, etc. The Design and Construction of a Front-end and Back-end Separated E-commerce Platform Based on Spring Boot and Vue.js are completed in this paper. Spring Boot is used on the back-end to get data from and write data to the Druid connection pool of the database via MyBatis-Plus. A stateless security authentication mechanism will be employed in Spring Security and JWT to protect the user\'s information and data. The entire business cycle of product selection and online payment in the system is built with the Alipay SDK, and it also has a forum community and activity reservation module. In order to enhance the power of sticking and using the platform, both e-commerce and social media will be combined.\\nIn line with the software engineering development specifications, this paper will present all links in the process of requirement analysis, system design and function implementation, system testing, etc. According to the test results, the core functions of the system are working properly, such as displaying products, managing shopping carts, processing orders and operating communities, and there is a good sense of interactivity and response speed. The construction of this system can provide a low-cost and highly scalable way to achieve the digitalisation of small and medium-sized enterprises, and it can also offer some references for the integrated application of modern Web architecture in e-commerce.\", \"language_detected\": \"english\", \"remaining_balance\": 425.4987}',40.2145,39.8470,'2026-05-16 17:24:36'),(61,1,'TEXT','english',NULL,'超级改写(260111_1_en_ja_ru)','With the deep integration of Internet technology and mobile payment, traditional monolithic e-commerce systems can hardly meet the current business demands for high concurrency, easy maintenance and strong interaction. This paper completes the design and construction of a front-end and back-end separated e-commerce platform based on Spring Boot and Vue.js. The back-end adopts the Spring Boot framework, combined with MyBatis-Plus to achieve efficient data persistence, and optimizes database performance through the Druid connection pool. A stateless security authentication mechanism is established using Spring Security and JWT to ensure the security of user information and transactions. The system integrates Alipay SDK to realize the complete business cycle from product selection to online payment, and also incorporates forum community and activity reservation modules. By building a content ecosystem in the \"e-commerce + social\" model, it effectively enhances user stickiness and the interactive depth of the platform.\nIn strict accordance with software engineering development specifications, this paper discusses the whole process from requirement analysis, system design and function implementation to system testing. Test results show that the system stably supports core functions such as product display, shopping cart management, order processing and community interaction, and delivers favorable interactive experience and response speed. The development of this system provides small and medium-sized merchants with a low-cost and scalable solution for digital transformation, and also offers practical references for the integrated application of modern Web architectures in the e-commerce field','Driven by the profound fusion of Internet innovations and mobile finance, conventional monolithic e-commerce architectures struggle to satisfy contemporary commercial requirements regarding peak throughput, streamlined upkeep, and robust engagement. This research accomplishes the architecture and implementation of a front-end/back-end decoupled e-commerce framework utilizing Spring Boot and Vue.js. The server-side utilizes the Spring Boot structure, integrated with MyBatis-Plus for rapid data storage, and enhances database efficiency via the Druid connection pool. A stateless validation protection system is constructed employing Spring Security and JWT to guarantee the integrity of client data and financial operations. This application integrates Alipay SDK to facilitate the entire commercial flow from item picking to digital settlement, while also including discussion forums and event scheduling features. By establishing a content ecosystem within the \"e-commerce + social\" paradigm, it significantly improves consumer loyalty and the participatory intensity of the site.\nFollowing rigorous software engineering construction standards, this article examines the entire workflow ranging from requirement evaluation, architecture planning and feature realization to system validation. Evaluation outcomes demonstrate that the platform consistently facilitates primary modules like item presentation, cart administration, transaction handling and forum engagement, while delivering positive user interaction and processing velocity. The creation of this framework offers minor and medium-sized traders a budget-friendly and extensible approach for digital evolution, and likewise provides empirical benchmarks for the combined utilization of contemporary Web structures within the e-commerce sector.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,245,0.3675,'{\"cost\": 0.1078, \"success\": true, \"request_id\": \"1693c501-75ca-41ee-997d-b0aeab0c5448\", \"preset_name\": \"超级改写(260111_1_en_ja_ru)\", \"preset_used\": \"jc_muti_language_1\", \"original_text\": \"With the deep integration of Internet technology and mobile payment, traditional monolithic e-commerce systems can hardly meet the current business demands for high concurrency, easy maintenance and strong interaction. This paper completes the design and construction of a front-end and back-end separated e-commerce platform based on Spring Boot and Vue.js. The back-end adopts the Spring Boot framework, combined with MyBatis-Plus to achieve efficient data persistence, and optimizes database performance through the Druid connection pool. A stateless security authentication mechanism is established using Spring Security and JWT to ensure the security of user information and transactions. The system integrates Alipay SDK to realize the complete business cycle from product selection to online payment, and also incorporates forum community and activity reservation modules. By building a content ecosystem in the \\\"e-commerce + social\\\" model, it effectively enhances user stickiness and the interactive depth of the platform.\\nIn strict accordance with software engineering development specifications, this paper discusses the whole process from requirement analysis, system design and function implementation to system testing. Test results show that the system stably supports core functions such as product display, shopping cart management, order processing and community interaction, and delivers favorable interactive experience and response speed. The development of this system provides small and medium-sized merchants with a low-cost and scalable solution for digital transformation, and also offers practical references for the integrated application of modern Web architectures in the e-commerce field\", \"processing_time\": 49.93, \"characters_count\": 245, \"paraphrased_text\": \"Driven by the profound fusion of Internet innovations and mobile finance, conventional monolithic e-commerce architectures struggle to satisfy contemporary commercial requirements regarding peak throughput, streamlined upkeep, and robust engagement. This research accomplishes the architecture and implementation of a front-end/back-end decoupled e-commerce framework utilizing Spring Boot and Vue.js. The server-side utilizes the Spring Boot structure, integrated with MyBatis-Plus for rapid data storage, and enhances database efficiency via the Druid connection pool. A stateless validation protection system is constructed employing Spring Security and JWT to guarantee the integrity of client data and financial operations. This application integrates Alipay SDK to facilitate the entire commercial flow from item picking to digital settlement, while also including discussion forums and event scheduling features. By establishing a content ecosystem within the \\\"e-commerce + social\\\" paradigm, it significantly improves consumer loyalty and the participatory intensity of the site.\\nFollowing rigorous software engineering construction standards, this article examines the entire workflow ranging from requirement evaluation, architecture planning and feature realization to system validation. Evaluation outcomes demonstrate that the platform consistently facilitates primary modules like item presentation, cart administration, transaction handling and forum engagement, while delivering positive user interaction and processing velocity. The creation of this framework offers minor and medium-sized traders a budget-friendly and extensible approach for digital evolution, and likewise provides empirical benchmarks for the combined utilization of contemporary Web structures within the e-commerce sector.\", \"language_detected\": \"english\", \"remaining_balance\": 425.3655}',39.4660,39.0985,'2026-05-16 17:25:32'),(62,1,'TEXT','chinese',NULL,'降重模式0325-1','在互联网与移动支付深度融合的过程中，电子商务已成为国民经济的主要支柱，消费习惯有所变迁，使用户对购物平台的响应速度、交互体验及安全性提出了更高要求[1]，传统单体架构系统在应对大规模并发、复杂业务逻辑的过程中，暴露出扩展性不好、耦合性强以及维护成本高的局限，很难满足现代电商业务快速迭代的需要[2]。\n软件开发领域正朝着轻量化、模块化转变，围绕Spring Boot核心的架构思想同MyBatis-Plus等高效持久层框架，为高性能系统开发给予了技术支撑[3]，第三方支付接口标准化极大地使交易成本下降，在现有的这种背景之下，利用Java体系来开发一套把商品管理、订单处理和社区互动结合起来的前后端分离电商平台，既跟从技术发展趋势，也可有效满足市场对多元购物场景的实际需要','随着互联网与移动支付技术的深度融合，电子商务已演变为支撑国民经济的关键支柱产业。消费者行为模式的转型推动了对电商平台在响应效率、交互性能及数据安全方面的更高标准要求。传统单体架构因难以应对高并发访问和复杂的业务逻辑，在可扩展性、模块化程度以及运维成本方面表现出显著不足，这使其难以适应电商领域快速迭代的技术发展需求。\n当前软件开发领域正呈现出轻量化与模块化的显著趋势，以Spring Boot为代表的微服务架构框架，配合MyBatis-Plus等高效持久层工具，为高性能系统的构建提供了重要技术支持。第三方支付接口的标准化进程进一步降低了交易成本。在此背景下，基于Java技术栈开发集商品管理、订单处理及社区交互功能于一体的前后端分离型电商平台，不仅顺应了行业技术创新的方向，还能够精准对接多维购物场景的实际需求，从而实现市场价值的有效提升。',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,280,0.4200,'{\"cost\": 0.14, \"success\": true, \"request_id\": \"ec4667ba-7758-453e-ba2d-2a437311aee4\", \"preset_name\": \"降重模式0325-1\", \"preset_used\": \"zh_jc_1_0325\", \"original_text\": \"在互联网与移动支付深度融合的过程中，电子商务已成为国民经济的主要支柱，消费习惯有所变迁，使用户对购物平台的响应速度、交互体验及安全性提出了更高要求[1]，传统单体架构系统在应对大规模并发、复杂业务逻辑的过程中，暴露出扩展性不好、耦合性强以及维护成本高的局限，很难满足现代电商业务快速迭代的需要[2]。\\n软件开发领域正朝着轻量化、模块化转变，围绕Spring Boot核心的架构思想同MyBatis-Plus等高效持久层框架，为高性能系统开发给予了技术支撑[3]，第三方支付接口标准化极大地使交易成本下降，在现有的这种背景之下，利用Java体系来开发一套把商品管理、订单处理和社区互动结合起来的前后端分离电商平台，既跟从技术发展趋势，也可有效满足市场对多元购物场景的实际需要\", \"processing_time\": 0.85, \"characters_count\": 280, \"paraphrased_text\": \"随着互联网与移动支付技术的深度融合，电子商务已演变为支撑国民经济的关键支柱产业。消费者行为模式的转型推动了对电商平台在响应效率、交互性能及数据安全方面的更高标准要求。传统单体架构因难以应对高并发访问和复杂的业务逻辑，在可扩展性、模块化程度以及运维成本方面表现出显著不足，这使其难以适应电商领域快速迭代的技术发展需求。\\n当前软件开发领域正呈现出轻量化与模块化的显著趋势，以Spring Boot为代表的微服务架构框架，配合MyBatis-Plus等高效持久层工具，为高性能系统的构建提供了重要技术支持。第三方支付接口的标准化进程进一步降低了交易成本。在此背景下，基于Java技术栈开发集商品管理、订单处理及社区交互功能于一体的前后端分离型电商平台，不仅顺应了行业技术创新的方向，还能够精准对接多维购物场景的实际需求，从而实现市场价值的有效提升。\", \"language_detected\": \"chinese\", \"remaining_balance\": 425.2028}',38.7580,38.3380,'2026-05-16 17:25:50'),(63,1,'TEXT','chinese',NULL,'双降260112_1','在互联网与移动支付深度融合的过程中，电子商务已成为国民经济的主要支柱，消费习惯有所变迁，使用户对购物平台的响应速度、交互体验及安全性提出了更高要求[1]，传统单体架构系统在应对大规模并发、复杂业务逻辑的过程中，暴露出扩展性不好、耦合性强以及维护成本高的局限，很难满足现代电商业务快速迭代的需要[2]。\n软件开发领域正朝着轻量化、模块化转变，围绕Spring Boot核心的架构思想同MyBatis-Plus等高效持久层框架，为高性能系统开发给予了技术支撑[3]，第三方支付接口标准化极大地使交易成本下降，在现有的这种背景之下，利用Java体系来开发一套把商品管理、订单处理和社区互动结合起来的前后端分离电商平台，既跟从技术发展趋势，也可有效满足市场对多元购物场景的实际需要','在互联网技术和移动支付不断融合发展的背景下，电子商务已经成为了拉动国民经济增长的重要力量。在此情况下，消费者对于在线购物平台的服务品质、响应速度和安全保障要求越来越高[1]。传统的单体架构系统由于存在着扩展性差、模块之间强耦合、运维成本高这些固有的缺点，在面对电商领域不断增多的业务需求和技术变革的时候，已经不能满足要求了[2]。此种情况急需创建起新的分布式架构体系来应对现代商业环境对于灵活、高效的要求。\n软件开发越来越趋向于轻量化、模块化，以Spring Boot为代表的微服务架构框架加上MyBatis-Plus这样的高效数据访问工具，给高性能系统创建赋予了强有力的支撑。第三方支付接口标准化创建极大地缩减了交易费用。在这种背景下，在Java生态下开发融合商品管理、订单处理、社区互动等各方面的前后端分离型电商平台，既符合技术发展潮流，也能够适应各种消费场景的需求，具有很好的应用前景和市场前景。',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,280,0.4200,'{\"cost\": 0.1232, \"success\": true, \"request_id\": \"b3252a31-7ddb-43e5-94ff-e759894fe691\", \"preset_name\": \"双降260112_1\", \"preset_used\": \"aigcmove_sj_s_1\", \"original_text\": \"在互联网与移动支付深度融合的过程中，电子商务已成为国民经济的主要支柱，消费习惯有所变迁，使用户对购物平台的响应速度、交互体验及安全性提出了更高要求[1]，传统单体架构系统在应对大规模并发、复杂业务逻辑的过程中，暴露出扩展性不好、耦合性强以及维护成本高的局限，很难满足现代电商业务快速迭代的需要[2]。\\n软件开发领域正朝着轻量化、模块化转变，围绕Spring Boot核心的架构思想同MyBatis-Plus等高效持久层框架，为高性能系统开发给予了技术支撑[3]，第三方支付接口标准化极大地使交易成本下降，在现有的这种背景之下，利用Java体系来开发一套把商品管理、订单处理和社区互动结合起来的前后端分离电商平台，既跟从技术发展趋势，也可有效满足市场对多元购物场景的实际需要\", \"processing_time\": 2.96, \"characters_count\": 280, \"paraphrased_text\": \"在互联网技术和移动支付不断融合发展的背景下，电子商务已经成为了拉动国民经济增长的重要力量。在此情况下，消费者对于在线购物平台的服务品质、响应速度和安全保障要求越来越高[1]。传统的单体架构系统由于存在着扩展性差、模块之间强耦合、运维成本高这些固有的缺点，在面对电商领域不断增多的业务需求和技术变革的时候，已经不能满足要求了[2]。此种情况急需创建起新的分布式架构体系来应对现代商业环境对于灵活、高效的要求。\\n软件开发越来越趋向于轻量化、模块化，以Spring Boot为代表的微服务架构框架加上MyBatis-Plus这样的高效数据访问工具，给高性能系统创建赋予了强有力的支撑。第三方支付接口标准化创建极大地缩减了交易费用。在这种背景下，在Java生态下开发融合商品管理、订单处理、社区互动等各方面的前后端分离型电商平台，既符合技术发展潮流，也能够适应各种消费场景的需求，具有很好的应用前景和市场前景。\", \"language_detected\": \"chinese\", \"remaining_balance\": 425.0469}',37.8475,37.4275,'2026-05-16 17:26:01'),(64,1,'TEXT','english',NULL,'双降260206_en','With the deep integration of Internet technology and mobile payment, traditional monolithic e-commerce systems can hardly meet the current business demands for high concurrency, easy maintenance and strong interaction. This paper completes the design and construction of a front-end and back-end separated e-commerce platform based on Spring Boot and Vue.js. The back-end adopts the Spring Boot framework, combined with MyBatis-Plus to achieve efficient data persistence, and optimizes database performance through the Druid connection pool. A stateless security authentication mechanism is established using Spring Security and JWT to ensure the security of user information and transactions. The system integrates Alipay SDK to realize the complete business cycle from product selection to online payment, and also incorporates forum community and activity reservation modules. By building a content ecosystem in the \"e-commerce + social\" model, it effectively enhances user stickiness and the interactive depth of the platform.\nIn strict accordance with software engineering development specifications, this paper discusses the whole process from requirement analysis, system design and function implementation to system testing. Test results show that the system stably supports core functions such as product display, shopping cart management, order processing and community interaction, and delivers favorable interactive experience and response speed. The development of this system provides small and medium-sized merchants with a low-cost and scalable solution for digital transformation, and also offers practical references for the integrated application of modern Web architectures in the e-commerce field','With the development of the Internet and mobile finance, the old monolithic e-commerce structure is no longer suitable for meeting the high-traffic demands, simple operation and rich interactivity of today\'s times. Development and deployment of the decoupled front-end/back-end e-commerce system will be done with Spring Boot and Vue.js. To get fast data storage for the server side using MyBatis-Plus, Spring Boot will be used, and to increase the speed of the database connection manager, Druid has been selected. In order to build a stateless security verification system for the purpose of protecting user data privacy and business agreement with Spring Security and JWT, they will be employed. The Alipay SDK is used to carry out all links of the transaction, such as item selection and digital settlement, and a discussion forum and event booking have also been added. Through the construction of a content ecosystem under the \"e-commerce + social\" model, we hope to enhance the loyalty of consumers and increase their participation in the digital economy.\nIn accordance with the development standards for software engineering, this paper will conduct full-process analysis of requirements and Design, implementation, etc., as well as tests. Based on the evaluation results, the platform has consistently met the basic requirements for displaying goods, managing shopping carts, processing transactions and social functions, etc., and is also widely used by users and has good response speed. The building of this framework can help small and medium-sized enterprises access digitalisation in an affordable way and develop it according to their own circumstances; it will also provide some empirical data for the application of modern Web frameworks in e-commerce.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,245,0.3675,'{\"cost\": 0.1078, \"success\": true, \"request_id\": \"dba24e10-807f-4d03-867c-75740cd373b7\", \"preset_name\": \"双降260206_en\", \"preset_used\": \"5.09en\", \"original_text\": \"With the deep integration of Internet technology and mobile payment, traditional monolithic e-commerce systems can hardly meet the current business demands for high concurrency, easy maintenance and strong interaction. This paper completes the design and construction of a front-end and back-end separated e-commerce platform based on Spring Boot and Vue.js. The back-end adopts the Spring Boot framework, combined with MyBatis-Plus to achieve efficient data persistence, and optimizes database performance through the Druid connection pool. A stateless security authentication mechanism is established using Spring Security and JWT to ensure the security of user information and transactions. The system integrates Alipay SDK to realize the complete business cycle from product selection to online payment, and also incorporates forum community and activity reservation modules. By building a content ecosystem in the \\\"e-commerce + social\\\" model, it effectively enhances user stickiness and the interactive depth of the platform.\\nIn strict accordance with software engineering development specifications, this paper discusses the whole process from requirement analysis, system design and function implementation to system testing. Test results show that the system stably supports core functions such as product display, shopping cart management, order processing and community interaction, and delivers favorable interactive experience and response speed. The development of this system provides small and medium-sized merchants with a low-cost and scalable solution for digital transformation, and also offers practical references for the integrated application of modern Web architectures in the e-commerce field\", \"processing_time\": 56.15, \"characters_count\": 245, \"paraphrased_text\": \"With the development of the Internet and mobile finance, the old monolithic e-commerce structure is no longer suitable for meeting the high-traffic demands, simple operation and rich interactivity of today\'s times. Development and deployment of the decoupled front-end/back-end e-commerce system will be done with Spring Boot and Vue.js. To get fast data storage for the server side using MyBatis-Plus, Spring Boot will be used, and to increase the speed of the database connection manager, Druid has been selected. In order to build a stateless security verification system for the purpose of protecting user data privacy and business agreement with Spring Security and JWT, they will be employed. The Alipay SDK is used to carry out all links of the transaction, such as item selection and digital settlement, and a discussion forum and event booking have also been added. Through the construction of a content ecosystem under the \\\"e-commerce + social\\\" model, we hope to enhance the loyalty of consumers and increase their participation in the digital economy.\\nIn accordance with the development standards for software engineering, this paper will conduct full-process analysis of requirements and Design, implementation, etc., as well as tests. Based on the evaluation results, the platform has consistently met the basic requirements for displaying goods, managing shopping carts, processing transactions and social functions, etc., and is also widely used by users and has good response speed. The building of this framework can help small and medium-sized enterprises access digitalisation in an affordable way and develop it according to their own circumstances; it will also provide some empirical data for the application of modern Web frameworks in e-commerce.\", \"language_detected\": \"english\", \"remaining_balance\": 424.9045}',36.9085,36.5410,'2026-05-16 17:27:14'),(65,1,'TEXT','english',NULL,'双降260206_en','With the deep integration of Internet technology and mobile payment, traditional monolithic e-commerce systems can hardly meet the current business demands for high concurrency, easy maintenance and strong interaction. This paper completes the design and construction of a front-end and back-end separated e-commerce platform based on Spring Boot and Vue.js. The back-end adopts the Spring Boot framework, combined with MyBatis-Plus to achieve efficient data persistence, and optimizes database performance through the Druid connection pool. A stateless security authentication mechanism is established using Spring Security and JWT to ensure the security of user information and transactions. The system integrates Alipay SDK to realize the complete business cycle from product selection to online payment, and also incorporates forum community and activity reservation modules. By building a content ecosystem in the \"e-commerce + social\" model, it effectively enhances user stickiness and the interactive depth of the platform.\nIn strict accordance with software engineering development specifications, this paper discusses the whole process from requirement analysis, system design and function implementation to system testing. Test results show that the system stably supports core functions such as product display, shopping cart management, order processing and community interaction, and delivers favorable interactive experience and response speed. The development of this system provides small and medium-sized merchants with a low-cost and scalable solution for digital transformation, and also offers practical references for the integrated application of modern Web architectures in the e-commerce field','With the strong momentum of Internet innovation and mobile finance, the old single-module e-commerce structure is no longer capable of meeting the new requirements for high traffic, convenience of use, stability and security by enterprises today. The Development and Application of a Decoupled Front-end/Back-end E-commerce Framework Based on Spring Boot and Vue.js. Spring Boot is used for the server part, MyBatis-Plus is employed to write data in the database efficiently, and Druid Connection Manager can speed up the database. In order to protect the security of users\' information and their financial details, a stateless identity verification system based on Spring Security and JWT will be constructed. The whole commercial process of the Alipay SDK has been built according to this architecture to cover item browsing, digital settlement, and so on; a bulletin board system and event booking function have also been added. Build a media ecosystem based on the \"commerce + social\" model to increase the sticky factor of customers and promote more interactions with the service.\nAccording to the strictness of software engineering methodology, this paper will present all links in the process, such as requirement analysis and design, system construction, testing, etc. Based on the above evaluation results, it has been determined that the platform can reliably perform basic functions such as displaying products, managing shopping carts, processing orders and providing social services, and it has a good user interface and response speed. The construction of this framework is a low-cost, flexible model for the digitalisation of micro and small enterprises in the digital economy, and it can also provide empirical data on how to integrate various Web technologies comprehensively in e-commerce.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,245,0.3675,'{\"cost\": 0.1078, \"success\": true, \"request_id\": \"43d2270f-2749-4845-b9ba-ff93f34e6a37\", \"preset_name\": \"双降260206_en\", \"preset_used\": \"5.09en\", \"original_text\": \"With the deep integration of Internet technology and mobile payment, traditional monolithic e-commerce systems can hardly meet the current business demands for high concurrency, easy maintenance and strong interaction. This paper completes the design and construction of a front-end and back-end separated e-commerce platform based on Spring Boot and Vue.js. The back-end adopts the Spring Boot framework, combined with MyBatis-Plus to achieve efficient data persistence, and optimizes database performance through the Druid connection pool. A stateless security authentication mechanism is established using Spring Security and JWT to ensure the security of user information and transactions. The system integrates Alipay SDK to realize the complete business cycle from product selection to online payment, and also incorporates forum community and activity reservation modules. By building a content ecosystem in the \\\"e-commerce + social\\\" model, it effectively enhances user stickiness and the interactive depth of the platform.\\nIn strict accordance with software engineering development specifications, this paper discusses the whole process from requirement analysis, system design and function implementation to system testing. Test results show that the system stably supports core functions such as product display, shopping cart management, order processing and community interaction, and delivers favorable interactive experience and response speed. The development of this system provides small and medium-sized merchants with a low-cost and scalable solution for digital transformation, and also offers practical references for the integrated application of modern Web architectures in the e-commerce field\", \"processing_time\": 56.96, \"characters_count\": 245, \"paraphrased_text\": \"With the strong momentum of Internet innovation and mobile finance, the old single-module e-commerce structure is no longer capable of meeting the new requirements for high traffic, convenience of use, stability and security by enterprises today. The Development and Application of a Decoupled Front-end/Back-end E-commerce Framework Based on Spring Boot and Vue.js. Spring Boot is used for the server part, MyBatis-Plus is employed to write data in the database efficiently, and Druid Connection Manager can speed up the database. In order to protect the security of users\' information and their financial details, a stateless identity verification system based on Spring Security and JWT will be constructed. The whole commercial process of the Alipay SDK has been built according to this architecture to cover item browsing, digital settlement, and so on; a bulletin board system and event booking function have also been added. Build a media ecosystem based on the \\\"commerce + social\\\" model to increase the sticky factor of customers and promote more interactions with the service.\\nAccording to the strictness of software engineering methodology, this paper will present all links in the process, such as requirement analysis and design, system construction, testing, etc. Based on the above evaluation results, it has been determined that the platform can reliably perform basic functions such as displaying products, managing shopping carts, processing orders and providing social services, and it has a good user interface and response speed. The construction of this framework is a low-cost, flexible model for the digitalisation of micro and small enterprises in the digital economy, and it can also provide empirical data on how to integrate various Web technologies comprehensively in e-commerce.\", \"language_detected\": \"english\", \"remaining_balance\": 424.7698}',36.1375,35.7700,'2026-05-16 17:28:24'),(66,1,'TEXT','english',NULL,'双降260206_en','With the deep integration of Internet technology and mobile payment, traditional monolithic e-commerce systems can hardly meet the current business demands for high concurrency, easy maintenance and strong interaction. This paper completes the design and construction of a front-end and back-end separated e-commerce platform based on Spring Boot and Vue.js. The back-end adopts the Spring Boot framework, combined with MyBatis-Plus to achieve efficient data persistence, and optimizes database performance through the Druid connection pool. A stateless security authentication mechanism is established using Spring Security and JWT to ensure the security of user information and transactions. The system integrates Alipay SDK to realize the complete business cycle from product selection to online payment, and also incorporates forum community and activity reservation modules. By building a content ecosystem in the \"e-commerce + social\" model, it effectively enhances user stickiness and the interactive depth of the platform.\nIn strict accordance with software engineering development specifications, this paper discusses the whole process from requirement analysis, system design and function implementation to system testing. Test results show that the system stably supports core functions such as product display, shopping cart management, order processing and community interaction, and delivers favorable interactive experience and response speed. The development of this system provides small and medium-sized merchants with a low-cost and scalable solution for digital transformation, and also offers practical references for the integrated application of modern Web architectures in the e-commerce field','Due to the close relationship between Internet innovation and mobile commerce, the old monolithic e-commerce architecture is unable to meet the new demands of high concurrency, simple operation and powerful functions for modern commerce. The structure and execution of the separated front-end and back-end e-commerce system based on Spring Boot and Vue.js are introduced in this article. Spring Boot will be used for the back end, and then MyBatis-Plus will be employed to carry out high-speed database read and write operations through Druid. To enhance the security of data for users and the company, Spring Security and JWT have been used to build a stateless authentication system. The Alipay SDK is used in all parts of the business process of this platform for item selection and digital payment, and it also has a forum community and event scheduling function. Construct a content ecosystem based on the \"e-commerce + social\" model to improve the sense of belonging and use for consumers of services.\nIn line with the software engineering development standard, this paper will introduce the whole process of requirements analysis, system architecture and function realisation and system verification. Based on the evaluation results, the framework can reliably support the basic functions of item display, cart management, order processing and social functions, and it is simple to use and fast. The construction of this platform can provide small and medium-sized traders with a low-cost, flexible way to go digital, and at the same time, it will provide some data for the unified application of existing Web frameworks in the e-commerce industry.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,245,0.3675,'{\"cost\": 0.1078, \"success\": true, \"request_id\": \"be07bfba-cc55-456a-bb56-5415a9d43140\", \"preset_name\": \"双降260206_en\", \"preset_used\": \"5.09en\", \"original_text\": \"With the deep integration of Internet technology and mobile payment, traditional monolithic e-commerce systems can hardly meet the current business demands for high concurrency, easy maintenance and strong interaction. This paper completes the design and construction of a front-end and back-end separated e-commerce platform based on Spring Boot and Vue.js. The back-end adopts the Spring Boot framework, combined with MyBatis-Plus to achieve efficient data persistence, and optimizes database performance through the Druid connection pool. A stateless security authentication mechanism is established using Spring Security and JWT to ensure the security of user information and transactions. The system integrates Alipay SDK to realize the complete business cycle from product selection to online payment, and also incorporates forum community and activity reservation modules. By building a content ecosystem in the \\\"e-commerce + social\\\" model, it effectively enhances user stickiness and the interactive depth of the platform.\\nIn strict accordance with software engineering development specifications, this paper discusses the whole process from requirement analysis, system design and function implementation to system testing. Test results show that the system stably supports core functions such as product display, shopping cart management, order processing and community interaction, and delivers favorable interactive experience and response speed. The development of this system provides small and medium-sized merchants with a low-cost and scalable solution for digital transformation, and also offers practical references for the integrated application of modern Web architectures in the e-commerce field\", \"processing_time\": 23.68, \"characters_count\": 245, \"paraphrased_text\": \"Due to the close relationship between Internet innovation and mobile commerce, the old monolithic e-commerce architecture is unable to meet the new demands of high concurrency, simple operation and powerful functions for modern commerce. The structure and execution of the separated front-end and back-end e-commerce system based on Spring Boot and Vue.js are introduced in this article. Spring Boot will be used for the back end, and then MyBatis-Plus will be employed to carry out high-speed database read and write operations through Druid. To enhance the security of data for users and the company, Spring Security and JWT have been used to build a stateless authentication system. The Alipay SDK is used in all parts of the business process of this platform for item selection and digital payment, and it also has a forum community and event scheduling function. Construct a content ecosystem based on the \\\"e-commerce + social\\\" model to improve the sense of belonging and use for consumers of services.\\nIn line with the software engineering development standard, this paper will introduce the whole process of requirements analysis, system architecture and function realisation and system verification. Based on the evaluation results, the framework can reliably support the basic functions of item display, cart management, order processing and social functions, and it is simple to use and fast. The construction of this platform can provide small and medium-sized traders with a low-cost, flexible way to go digital, and at the same time, it will provide some data for the unified application of existing Web frameworks in the e-commerce industry.\", \"language_detected\": \"english\", \"remaining_balance\": 424.6347}',35.3605,34.9930,'2026-05-16 17:28:57'),(67,1,'TEXT','chinese',NULL,'AI移除_260112_1 (降AI能力一般，改写幅度小，学术性强，非一逗到底）','在理论层面之上，本课题对加深现代化Web架构集成逻辑的理解有作用，通过把Spring Security、JWT跟持久层框架整合，可系统地探究分布式环境下身份校验和权限控制的机制，探讨如何借助逻辑分层与配置优化使系统的抗压和容错能力得以增强[4]，针对订单状态机流转、支付回调验证等核心业务做的研究，可为同类电商系统的架构设计给予参考范例，助力技术方案于具体应用场景中的沉淀和演进[5]。\n在实际应用的相关方面，本系统为中小商家推出了低成本、高效率的数字化方案，借助把支付宝模块和后台管理功能集成，商家能达成从商品上架到结算的整个流程自动化，有效减少人工干预造成的风险[6]，系统引入了个论坛社区模块，借助社交互动使用户粘性提升，搭建“内容+电商”的新型交互体系，这种把购物与社交属性相结合的设计，对于提升用户体验、降低获客成本起到直接推动效果，拥有良好的市场推广价值','从理论角度来讲，本课题对深化现代化Web架构集成逻辑的认识有益，经由将Spring Security、JWT同持久层框架融合起来，可以全面探究分布式环境下身份认证及权限把控的机制，探寻怎样依靠逻辑分层并加强配置来提升系统的抗压和容错水平[4]，就订单状态机流转、支付回调验证这类关键业务展开研究，能够为同类型电商系统架构的设计给予参照范例，推动技术方案在实际应用场合里的沉淀和演进[5]。\n本系统给中小商家提供了一种低成本、高效率的数字化解决方案，通过将支付宝模块和后台管理系统集成起来，商家可以实现商品上架、结算等全流程的自动化操作，从而减少人工干预所造成的风险[6]，系统中引入了论坛社区模块，利用社交互动来提高用户的粘性，构建起“内容+电商”的新交互模式，该种将购物与社交属性结合的设计方式，对于改善用户体验、削减获客成本有着直接的促进作用，具备较好的市场推广价值',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,327,0.4905,'{\"cost\": 0.1439, \"success\": true, \"request_id\": \"75c85ec3-159c-4f1e-b7d7-63e07d1575e4\", \"preset_name\": \"AI移除_260112_1 (降AI能力一般，改写幅度小，学术性强，非一逗到底）\", \"preset_used\": \"aigcmove_tp_s_1\", \"original_text\": \"在理论层面之上，本课题对加深现代化Web架构集成逻辑的理解有作用，通过把Spring Security、JWT跟持久层框架整合，可系统地探究分布式环境下身份校验和权限控制的机制，探讨如何借助逻辑分层与配置优化使系统的抗压和容错能力得以增强[4]，针对订单状态机流转、支付回调验证等核心业务做的研究，可为同类电商系统的架构设计给予参考范例，助力技术方案于具体应用场景中的沉淀和演进[5]。\\n在实际应用的相关方面，本系统为中小商家推出了低成本、高效率的数字化方案，借助把支付宝模块和后台管理功能集成，商家能达成从商品上架到结算的整个流程自动化，有效减少人工干预造成的风险[6]，系统引入了个论坛社区模块，借助社交互动使用户粘性提升，搭建“内容+电商”的新型交互体系，这种把购物与社交属性相结合的设计，对于提升用户体验、降低获客成本